			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				this is long<BR>
<BR>
The cleric is one of the most useful, multi faceted classes. I will not subscribe to the idea Clerics are only good to sit on their rears in a group. First off soloing is hard but not impossible, defiantly not worth the time if you can get into a group. But as I am sure most people have notices this game makes people selfish. The most important thing to most people here is XP so if there is a group of 2 people in a good camp XP'ing safely they will most of the time never let people join their group.. and no not even a cleric. I have soloed allot and yelled out for a group many times in all sorts of zones to nothing but silence. WE HAVE to learn to solo. The best way I have learned to solo is based on the Mob. Considering the Mob I either root and DD it to almost death &lt;for those hard hitters&gt; , or I root, siphon str, nuke then engage, nuking based on how much I'm getting hit.  If I am able to do the later I usually end up with a good balance of HTP and mana left so I med allot less.<BR>
<BR>
Now for a Clerics role in a group, none has mentioned when a group consists of mostly casters. Even most shamans I have met don't do much better than me in taking damage and asking an even con Rogue the other day realized I had more HTP's. When grouped with casters I often do allot of the tanking depending on my mana. I can hold the Crit with healing while I melee and keep the MOB off the caster's which aggro quick with their spells and suck up my mana cause they have so few HTP's.   Also in a group when a cleric's mana is pretty full any melee damage can help end a crits life quicker, not to mention when you come across caster MOBs playing interrupt with a quick weapon can do wonders for your groups livelihood. I have a Wraithbone hammer 8/28 and regardless of my mana often Ill jump on the Casting mobs and play interrupt and add a hundred or so damage in a relatively short time.<BR>
<BR>
You CAN have fun s a cleric, at lvl 22 I got so fed up and went to another server and played a SK to 19. Since I have come back and re appreciated my true class.<BR>
<BR>
but along with fun ALWAYS know when you must sit on your rear, because every death is on your hands. Do not nuke when you don't have to, I would much rather melee and maybe take a few hits, DD'ing only when the crit is almost dead or like in Dalnir when ya get one of those DE healers that need to be dead quick. Be smart and your group will respect you and never have any qualms about you meleeing or nuking.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
